Package edu.stanford.math.nebtda

Interface Summary
MetricSpace<T> Interface for a metric space.
Value<T> Interface for objects which can return a value, typically density.
 

Class Summary
AnglePenalty Abstract class for the angle penalty on a 1-cell, which acts as a smoothing force.
AnglePenaltyNone Implements the zero angle penalty on a 1-cell.
AnglePenaltyTrig Computes an angle penalty on a 1-cell.
Boundary Abstract class for the boundary of a higher dimensional cell.
BoundaryLoop Implements the boundary of a 2-cell as a piecewise linear loop.
Cell Abstract class for a cell.
Cell0 Implements a 0-cell.
Cell1 Implements a 1-cell.
CellHigher Implements a higher dimensional cell.
CellHigherNode Implements a node in a higher dimensional cell.
Cluster<T> Implements a cluster.
Clustering<T> Abstract class for a clustering method.
ClusteringSingleLinkage<T> Implements single-linkage clustering.
ClustRep<T> Abstract class for choosing a representative from a cluster.
ClustRepMaxValue<T> Chooses the representative with the highest value from a cluster.
Density Implements a density estimator for data.
Distribution Abstract class which declares the functionality of a distribution.
DistributionNormal Implements a normal distribution.
InitialBand Abstract class for generating initial bands.
InitialBandEuclidean Generates initial bands for general data sets in Euclidean space.
InitialBandLine Generates a straight line initial band.
InitialBandSphere Generates initial bands for datasets which are normalized to lie on a unit sphere.
IO Reads input and writes output.
NullOutputStream This OutputStream writes all data to the famous /dev/null.
Parameters0 Stores the parameters for 0-cell trials.
Parameters1 Stores the parameters for 1-cell trials.
ParametersHigher Stores the parameters for a higher dimensional cell trial.
Potential Abstract class for a differentiable potential function.
Tangent Abstract class for the tangent along a 1-cell.
TangentNaive Implements the naive tangent along a 1-cell, which is given by averaging the two adjacent edges.
TrialHelper Contains the tools for running trials.
Tuple<T1,T2> Implements an ordered pair.
VectorDouble Implements vectors in Euclidean space.
VectorDoubleComparator Compares vectors, based on the norm of the coordinate at a specified index.
